comments.body:
@artmello Thanks for the submit!  It doesn't look like you signed your commit.  If you could do 'git commit --amend -s' and then repush the submit, that would be great.  Also an added test or two to tests/rmi.bats would be awesome.

The code that you have looks good to me on the surface.  However Travis is failing with:

vendor/github.com/ostreedev/ostree-go/pkg/otremote/remoteadd.go:1:1: expected 'package', found 'EOF'
cmd/buildah/rmi.go:43::warning: cyclomatic complexity 41 of function rmiCmd() is high (> 40) (gocyclo)
make: *** [validate] Error 1

@rhatdan @nalind is this something we can override, or do we have to rework the code to get the number of if statements/checks down in that function?
